This paper deals with the development of a secure routing protocol for wireless sensor networks, which involves network security and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses different types of attacks and their impact on the network, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed protocol involves the use of trust-based mechanisms, which can be categorized under cs.LG (Learning). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures for routing, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes a protocol for mobile sensor networks, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
